Next Generation Sequencing (NGS) Market - Competitive and Segmentation Analysis:

**Segments**

- On the basis of product and service, the global next generation sequencing (NGS) market can be segmented into instruments, consumables, services, and workflow products.
- Based on technology, the market can be categorized into sequencing by synthesis, ion semiconductor sequencing, single-molecule real-time sequencing, nanopore sequencing, and other sequencing technologies.
- When considering application, the market can be divided into diagnostics, drug discovery, biomarker discovery, personalized medicine, agriculture and animal research, and other applications.
- By end user, the NGS market can be segmented into academic and research institutes, pharmaceutical and biotechnology companies, hospitals and clinics, and other end users.

